    "system_description": "English disambiguation under morphological poverty. English has almost no case marking (only pronoun case: he/him, she/her) and minimal verb agreement (only 3rd person singular -s). Disambiguation relies primarily on strict SVO word order — violation of SVO without auxiliary marking leaves argument roles unresolved. The auxiliary system (do-support for negation and questions, modal verbs, passivization with be) adds a secondary disambiguation layer. When word order and auxiliaries both fail, prosody and pragmatics must resolve.",
